import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Disease')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Cases')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wounds, other and disease cases over time?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    
    data[['wounds', 'other', 'disease']].plot.hist(alpha=0.5, bins=20)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of wounds, other and disease cases?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data.set_index('date', inplace=True)
    
    data_percentage = data.div(data.sum(axis=1), axis=0) * 100
    data_percentage[['wounds', 'other', 'disease']].plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=plt.gca())
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the percentage of each category of cases?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('date').mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Disease')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Average Number of Cases')

        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
